article.headline: San Diego St. 76, TCU 71
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- Brandon Heath scored 22 points and grabbed a team-high 10 rebounds in San Diego State's 76-71 victory over TCU on Wednesday night. Heath was 8-of-15 from the floor and 5-of-7 from the free throw line. Lorrenzo Wade had 19 points and six rebounds, while Mohamed Abukar came off the bench to add 17 points. The Aztecs (14-7, 4-4 Mountain West) led 40-34 at the break and turned 18 TCU turnovers into 26 points. TCU (10-10, 2-6) hit only 39 percent of their shots. Neiman Owens and Ryan Wall led the Horned Frogs with 16 points each. Wall was 3-of-4 from 3-point range. Kevin Langford had 12 points and led the team with nine rebounds, while Brent Hackett scored 10 points.
